    "# HEART DISEASE PREDICTION: UNDERSTANDING THE PATIENT DATA \n",
    "### Part 1 of 4 -- Exploring Data Analysis \n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "Imagine you've just been handed a dataset from a hospital's cardiology department. 630,000 patient records, 14 clinical measurements each. The task: build a system that can flag patients likely to have heart disease before they even see a cariologist.\n",
    "\n",
    "Before writing a single line of model code, we need to understand what we've working with - not just statistically, but medically. Every feature here has a clinical story. Let's read it.\n",
    "\n",
    "*What you'll learn in this notebook:*\n",
    "\n",
    " * How to audit a clinical dataset for quality and completeness\n",
    " * Which patient attributes are most predictive of heart disease\n",
    " * How to visualize medical data in ways that reveal real patterns\n",
    " * Why class balance matters differently in healthcare than in competitions"
   ]
